𝑭𝒊𝒓𝒔𝒕 𝑳𝒂𝒔𝒉 𝑾𝒊𝒕𝒉 𝑴𝒆 𝒇𝒐𝒓 2023
In all complete honesty, this edit took me hours 🥵 lol

The turn out was so beautiful but my anxiety during the whole process was kicking my 🍑 
Let me explain how behind the scenes went.

⚠️My lighting was acting up in the beginning literally fixed it 5 + times 
⚠️My gooseneck tripod was stiffer than stiff that day (haha) 
⚠️My model kept laughing when I said pose and look at the camera so it took about 15 takes lol 🎬
⚠️This 30 second video took me 1 hour just to find an audio that fit best & 4 hours to figure out & edit.

Who said editing was easy & fun ?? 😂😂 Some are easier than others but it’s really all practice & being consistent. Even with all the madness, I remained determined & made it happen. One of my goals this year was to record alot of my sets & create as much content as possible. Sooo …. here’s the first one for 2023! 🤩 Let me know how I did✨

How long do you take to edit? Let’s chat in the comments ✨ FOLLOW FOR MORE CONTENT LIKE THIS🤍

LASH WITH ME: 
Let’s Do My Signature Strip Look Set

— Here’s a few things to always keep in mind when doing a Strip Look Set 👇🏼
1. Your spikes can make or break this set. Make sure you are using the right lengths on your top/middle layer so they don’t get lost! 
2. Direction Is Key! ⚠️ no crooked spikes allowed! 
3. Keep your spike thickness consistent so it looks the same throughout the set and NEAT! 
4. MAP OUT your set to better guide you! 
5. Last but not LEAST! Take your time!!!

TIPS TO HELP YOU RECREATE THIS SET.

• use a mirror to help you check out the direction & also spacing between the spikes. 
They shouldn’t be too close nor too far from each other.

Hot minute! But your girl got back in motivation mode so that means it’s time to CREATE! 
Trust me, I know how overwhelming it can get sometimes creating content but in order to see growth, we have to be consistent. Here’s some tips to keep in mind that can help you create valuable content along the way. 

📸 Short Videos
- create 5-7 second reels whenever you don’t feel like creating long videos. Instagram now rewards watch time, so naturally, when you make shorter videos, your watch time will be higher. 

📸 Have strong Hooks 
- transform a weak hook into a strong hook. 
Example: Weak hook “ best ways to grow on Instagram”
Instead 👉🏼 Strong hook “ Avoid these mistakes if you want to grow on Instagram” 

📸 - create shareable content
- remember that most interactions on instagram occurs in direct message (DMS) craft your content in a way

📸 - record in high quality. 
You should be recording in 4k60fps to get the best quality on your feed. When using third party apps to edit (CapCut, InShot” compress your video into 1080p 60fps as it’s the highest that Instagram supports without making your video blurry. Get some good lighting, purchase a tripod & record different angles. There’s too much competition for you to be doing the bare minimum 🤷🏻‍♀️ 

📸 lastly, engage with your audience 
- respond to comments and DMS. This will foster better connections and build a stronger community for you. 

Hope this helped 🫶🏼

We all make the excuses that we can’t create content because you think you need an expensive camera. Well, I’m here to tell you, your iPhone is just fine. 

Here’s 6 tips that can help you. 

1. First & foremost, let’s start off by making sure we clean our camera lens. I can’t explain how important it is that you take that first step to make sure your lens is clean. If you record on a dirty screen, there no coming back from that. 

2. Make sure your camera settings match the quality. Shoot at 4k60fps directly from your iPhone. Just go to your iPhone settings.

3. Turn your HDR video off. Go to settings > search “HDR” > turn off. This gives a weird dark color to the videos and photos. 

4. When using third party apps such as (CapCut, InShot etc) make sure you are downloading it as 1080p 30fps as it is what IG supports at the moment. Avoid downloading them in 4k as IG will suppress your video and mess up your quality making it dark & blurry. 

5. When recording your client, make sure to avoid background distractions. The focus should be on the clients face and not your lash cart in the back lol. To get a smooth video effect, make sure you pan out slowly when recording (stop moving your phone so fast!) this will have your video looking all over the place if you don’t move smooth. 

6. LIGHTING! This is so important!! Make sure you are not recording against it. Whatever you are recording should be facing the light so you can get a crispy clear shot. 

Share & Save this for later.

Making it easier for you guys so that creating content can be more fun! Here’s simple and easy angles that I use that can help you when taking taking photos/videos of your clients. 

Side View Angle:
I prefer to do this while my client is laying down. 
This is a pretty shot to get a good angle of how the lashes look from the side.

Front View Angle: 
This is a great angle to showcase your full set. 
To do this, simply stand next to them from the side, angle your phone above them and pan from corner to corner slowly to get a good shot. 

Half Face Angle:
Focusing on one eye only
In order to do this I prefer to keep my client laying down. Bring your phone close up to their face (zoom if you have too) and snap 📸

Close Up Model Shot:
I love doing this close-up because it captures the entire set beautifully. To do this get in front of your client (do this behind a solid background or use a backdrop) tilt their head just a bit and take your shot. 

The Look Away Then Back:
This is such a great pose when you’re having fun with your clients and want something more sultry and sexy. To do this, simply stand behind a solid wall or backdrop, have them look away from the camera (when there’s head movement it looks better) then let them know when to look back. BOOM! beautiful shot 😍

Off Guard Pose:
This pose is similar to the side view angle, but instead the client is standing up. To do this, have your client stand behind a solid wall or backdrop, keep your phone straight, then prompt your client to look straight forward not at the camera. 🤗
